definitions: in a way that relates to a class or group of similar things; not specifically

examples.text: what most writers generically refer to as "world music"

shortDefinitions: in way that relates to class or group of similar things

examples.text: Prozac, generically known as fluoxetine hydrochloride
most shorts are made of a stretchy fabric generically called spandex

definitions: in a way which lacks imagination or individuality; predictably and unoriginally

examples.text: the characters were stiffly animated and generically designed
the group of aerobic bacteria generically designated as actinomycetes
